      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "Progressive colt PASTOR DUNBAR (6) took his record to four from five when successfully stepping up to Group 1 level with a fast-finishing NSW Derby win last start. Tackles older rivals tonight but he is a talented young trotter on the up. Hard to knock the form of KYVALLEY JUDGE (10) who has put a string of wins and placings together. Produced another fine effort last start when he finished second at Menangle and won his previous two Victorian appearances. Draws out a little on the second line and is first up for six weeks but was kept ticking over with a trial win. SAM NIEN (1) is first up for six months but has won when fresh before. Gets the ace draw and should be ready following three nice trials. JUST AS I AM (3) has been freshened since returning to winning form last start. Draws well and scored the last time he raced here.",
